thread.title: UH soccer blanked at UC Davis
thread.title_full: UH soccer blanked at UC Davis - Hawaii News - Honolulu Star-Advertiser

author: Star-Advertiser staff
title: UH soccer blanked at UC Davis
text:
The Hawaii soccer team yielded two goals in each half to UC Davis as its run of futility in Big West play continued in a 4-0 loss to the Aggies today in Davis, Calif. It was the third straight shutout defeat for the Rainbow Wahine (3-12-1, 0-6 Big West), who have two games left to try to avoid a winless conference season.
Defender Paige Okazaki received a red card early in the second half, causing the Wahine to play a woman down for the rest of the match. The Aggies, leading 2-0 at halftime, capitalized with two more scores.
UH dropped to 0-7 in mainland games this season. Its final road game of the season is Sunday at Long Beach State.
